cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DB

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on incorporating cryptography to enforce confidentiality and integrity policies on untrusted storage. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses leveraging the policy language of the IFC system to automatically use the appropriate keys and correct cryptographic operations. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) are possible categories as the paper presents a prototype implementation and a case study that demonstrate the practicality of the proposed system. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also a possible category as the paper specifically focuses on enforcing information flow control on key value stores.
